"Neguţ S., Neacşu M.C.","Industrial activity and environment protection. geopolitical and geoeconomical considerations regarding the kyoto protocol",2009,"Metalurgia International","14","SPEC. ISS. 15",,"5","12",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-73249146328&partnerID=40&md5=ad54daea23cfc40d120952b15fa28da4","Bucharest Academy of Economic Studies, Romania","Neguţ, S., Bucharest Academy of Economic Studies, Romania; Neacşu, M.C., Bucharest Academy of Economic Studies, Romania","An old problem - ""global"" environment changes, is today the subject and substance of heavy mediatisation. The image's myth is stronger than reality, but if the civic spirit becomes better and each citizen of the planet more responsible towards the environment, it still is good. The current study aims to analyse not only the geopolitical implications of dramatic environment changes, but also the so called ""protocols"" and ""agreements"" on this matter. Are these an instrument used to control the economic competitors? An answer to this question is attempted, in this article.","Environment; Geopolitics; Global environment changes; Global warming; Kyoto protocol",,,,,,,"Bǎlteanu, D., Şerban, M., Modificǎrile globale ale mediului. O evaluare interdisciplinarǎ a incertitudinilor/ Global environment changes (2005) An interdisciplinary evaluation of uncertainties, Editura Coresi, , Bucureşti; Hansen, J., Sato, M., Ruedy, R., Lacis, A., Valdar, O., Global warming in the twenty-first century: An alternative scenario (2000) Proceedings of the National Academy of Science, 97 (18); Neacşu, M. C., Conflictele lumii - analizǎ secvenţialǎ a sistemului geopolitic mondial la începutul mileniului III. Studiu de caz: Africa/World's conflicts - a sequential analysis of the global geopolitical system at the start of the third millennia. Case study: Africa, în Jurnalul Economic, anul VIII, nr. 15, 2005, pp. 45-55Neguţ, S.; Leca, A.; Papatulicǎ, M.; Vlad, L. B. Bogdan; Neacşu, M. C., Orientǎri 